## 8. Figma Integration (THE design source of truth)

Figma is where real design teams live. Credentials are configured in .env with OAuth scopes. Here is what is enabled and what each tool maps to.

### OAuth Scopes Available

- Users: read current user name, email, profile image
- Files: read comments, create/modify/delete comments, read file contents + render images, read file metadata, read version history, read individual components/styles, read published components/styles from files, read published components/styles from team libraries
- Development: read/list dev resources, create/modify dev resources
- Projects: read team project structure
- Webhooks: read/list, create/modify/delete webhooks

MISSING SCOPE: file_variables:read and file_variables:write are NOT listed. These are required for the Variables REST API endpoints (GET/POST /v1/files/:file_key/variables). Without these, get_figma_variables and update_figma_variables will fail. Add these scopes in the Figma app settings to enable bidirectional token sync with Prism.

### Authentication

OAuth client credentials flow, NOT a Personal Access Token.

Environment variables (already in .env):
- FIGMA_CLIENT_ID -- OAuth app client ID
- FIGMA_CLIENT_SECRET -- OAuth app client secret

Store both in Secret Manager. The agent runtime needs an OAuth token manager that:

1. Exchanges client credentials for an access_token + refresh_token via POST /v1/oauth/token
2. Caches the access_token (expires_in from response, typically 2 hours)
3. Auto-refreshes using the refresh_token before expiry
4. All Figma tool calls use the cached access_token in Authorization: Bearer header

New file: packages/agents/src/shared/figmaAuth.ts

```typescript
// Singleton OAuth token manager for Figma
// POST https://api.figma.com/v1/oauth/token
// grant_type: authorization_code (initial) or refresh_token (renewal)
// Cache in Redis: figma:access_token (TTL = expires_in - 60s buffer)
// All figmaTools.ts functions call getAccessToken() before each request
```

