  Agent receives event --> re-runs component audit, token comparison, visual regression
  Posts results as comments or creates tasks for the team

### Rate limit strategy:

Cache file reads in Redis (5 min TTL for file content, 30 min for components/styles).
Implement exponential backoff on 429 responses.
Batch node-specific requests to minimize file-level API calls.
Track rate limit headers (Retry-After, X-Figma-Rate-Limit-Type) per agent.

### Infrastructure:

No new services needed for Figma. Tools are HTTP calls from the existing agent runtime.
Store FIGMA_CLIENT_ID and FIGMA_CLIENT_SECRET in Secret Manager.
New file: packages/agents/src/shared/figmaAuth.ts for OAuth token lifecycle.
Add api.figma.com to allowed network egress domains.
Cache access tokens in Redis (key: figma:access_token, TTL: expires_in - 60s).

