## 9. Storybook Integration (component development and visual testing)

Setting up via `npm create storybook@latest`. Storybook is where the design team develops, documents, and visually tests components in isolation. Once deployed as a static site, agents interact with it via the screenshot service and its stories.json index.

### Storybook Setup

Run in the dashboard/Pulse frontend package:

```
cd packages/dashboard  # or packages/pulse
npm create storybook@latest
```

Scaffolds .storybook/ config and creates example stories. Team writes stories for every component in the design system. Deploy as a static site:

```
npx storybook build -o storybook-static
# Deploy to GCS bucket, Vercel, or Cloud Run static
```

Deployed URL becomes the base for all Storybook tools (e.g., https://storybook.glyphor.ai or internal Cloud Run URL).

### Storybook Tools

New file: packages/agents/src/shared/storybookTools.ts

Factory: createStorybookTools(agentRole, db, storybookBaseUrl)

storybook_list_stories -- All design team. Parse the Storybook index (stories.json) to list all stories. Returns: component name, story name, story kind, file path, args/controls definition. Answers: "what components have stories? what variants exist?"
Implementation: Fetch {storybookBaseUrl}/index.json (Storybook 7+) or /stories.json and parse.

storybook_screenshot -- All design team. Screenshot a specific story at a specific viewport. Parameters: story_id (from list), viewport (width/height), args (override controls to test variants), globals (theme: light/dark). Returns: base64 PNG. Better than screenshot_page because no page chrome, nav, or layout noise -- just the isolated component.
Implementation: Playwright navigates to {storybookBaseUrl}/iframe.html?id={story_id}&args={encoded_args}&globals=theme:{theme}, waits for render, captures screenshot.

storybook_screenshot_all -- Sofia (Design Critic). Screenshot ALL stories across ALL viewports. Comprehensive visual snapshot of the entire component library. Parameters: viewports (default: [375, 768, 1440]), globals (default: both light and dark themes). Returns: array of screenshots labeled by story_id, viewport, theme.
Implementation: Iterate index.json entries, call screenshot for each with concurrency limit (5-10 parallel).

storybook_visual_diff -- Sofia (Design Critic). Compare current story renders against approved baseline snapshots. Detects visual regressions across the component library. Returns: changed stories with diff images and pixel change percentage, new stories with no baseline, removed stories (stale baselines).
Implementation: Download baselines from GCS, render current stories, run pixelmatch per story. Generate diff images highlighting changed regions.

storybook_save_baseline -- Mia (VP Design). Save current story screenshots as the approved baseline for visual regression testing. Called after design review approves changes. YELLOW authority (overwrites baselines).
Implementation: Upload current screenshots to GCS bucket (gs://glyphor-company/storybook-baselines/{story_id}/{viewport}_{theme}.png).

storybook_check_coverage -- Ryan (Template Arch), Mia (VP Design). Compare component inventory against story coverage. Returns: components WITH stories, components WITHOUT stories (coverage gaps), stories for deleted components (stale). 
Implementation: Cross-reference list_components (code tool scans src/components/) with storybook_list_stories.

storybook_get_story_source -- Ryan (Template Arch), Ava (Frontend). Read the source code of a specific story file. Understand how a component is documented, what props/args are exercised, what edge cases are covered.
Implementation: read_frontend_file pointed at the story file path from index.json metadata.

### Storybook Workflows

Component development loop:
  Ryan scaffolds component (scaffold_component with_storybook=true) --> story file created alongside component --> Ava implements --> storybook_screenshot to preview in isolation --> Sofia runs storybook_visual_diff --> Mia reviews, saves baseline if approved

Visual regression on PRs:
  PR opened on feature/design-* branch --> Storybook rebuilt with branch changes --> storybook_screenshot_all at all viewports and themes --> storybook_visual_diff against main baselines --> results posted as PR comment or Figma comment --> Sofia reviews diffs, approves or flags regressions

Design system coverage audit:
  storybook_check_coverage --> find components without stories --> Ryan creates missing stories --> storybook_screenshot_all establishes baselines --> coverage report submitted to Mia

### Storybook Infrastructure

Deployment: static site build to GCS bucket or Vercel (same as dashboard).
Baseline storage: GCS bucket (gs://glyphor-company/storybook-baselines/).
Screenshot service: same Playwright Cloud Function used by screenshot_page. Storybook iframe URLs are just regular URLs.
Build trigger: include Storybook build in the dashboard/Pulse CI pipeline so stories stay current with component changes.

