## Infrastructure Requirements

### Screenshot/Audit Service (Phase 1-2)

Cloud Function or lightweight Cloud Run service with Puppeteer + Chromium:

POST /screenshot { url, viewport, full_page, selector, wait_for }
Returns: { image: base64, dimensions, load_time_ms }

POST /audit { url, type: lighthouse|accessibility, categories }
Returns: { scores, issues[] }

256MB memory, 30s timeout. Can share one container for screenshots + audits.
Needs network access to internal dashboard/Pulse URLs (same VPC or public with auth).

### Image Generation (Phase 4)

No new infra -- use existing OpenAI API key for DALL-E 3.
Brand-constrained mode prepends Prism colors and style rules to the prompt.

### Asset Storage (Phase 3)

GCS bucket (likely existing glyphor-company) with subfolder structure:
gs://glyphor-company/assets/ (icons/, illustrations/, heroes/, thumbnails/, avatars/, brand/)

### Figma (Phase 5)

No new services. HTTP calls from agent runtime to api.figma.com.
FIGMA_CLIENT_ID and FIGMA_CLIENT_SECRET in Secret Manager.
New figmaAuth.ts manages OAuth token lifecycle, caches access_token in Redis.
Add api.figma.com to network egress allowlist.

### Storybook (Phase 6)

Run `npm create storybook@latest` in frontend packages.
Build: `npx storybook build -o storybook-static` added to CI pipeline.
Deploy: static site to GCS bucket, Vercel, or Cloud Run.
Baselines: gs://glyphor-company/storybook-baselines/ for visual regression snapshots.
Screenshots use the same Playwright service from Phase 1.

