## Before vs After

### Before (current):

Directive: "Audit Pulse UI against Prism design system"

Mia: [no tools to look at Pulse] "Based on my understanding of the design system, I recommend checking color consistency, typography, and spacing..." [generic advice report]

Leo: [cannot see the UI] "I would suggest reviewing the hero section for visual hierarchy..." [theoretical feedback]

Sofia: [cannot run audits] "The design should follow WCAG 2.1 AA standards..." [guidelines, not an audit]

Ava: [cannot read code] "Frontend components should use the design token system..." [recommendations she cannot verify]

### After (with tools):

Mia decomposes:
- Leo: "Screenshot every Pulse page at 3 breakpoints. Flag visual issues."
- Sofia: "Run Lighthouse + accessibility on all pages. Run brand compliance."
- Ava: "Search codebase for hardcoded colors/fonts. Check bundle size."
- Ryan: "Validate tokens vs implementation. Check component usage patterns."

Leo: [calls screenshot_page for 8 URLs x 3 viewports] "Hero clipped on mobile. Sidebar overflows at 768px. Card grid doesn't reflow below 1024px." [submits with actual screenshots]

Sofia: [calls run_lighthouse, run_accessibility_audit, validate_brand_compliance] "Performance: 67/100 (hero image 2.4MB unoptimized). Accessibility: 4 critical WCAG violations. Brand: 12 hardcoded colors instead of Prism tokens." [submits with audit data]

Ava: [calls search_frontend_code, check_bundle_size, list_components] "23 hardcoded color values across 8 files. Bundle 1.8MB -- recharts is 40%. 6 dead components. 3 TypeScript errors." [submits with file paths and line numbers]

Ryan: [calls validate_tokens_vs_implementation, get_component_usage] "14 unused tokens. 8 components with inline styles. Button has 4 variants, 2 used. Spacing inconsistency: 16px vs 1rem." [submits with token mapping]

Mia consolidates: "3 critical issues, 23 medium. Created 12 tasks. Estimated 3 days critical, 5 days full compliance."

That is a real design team doing real work.

